# TypeScript / Next.js

- Keep TypeScript strict; do not introduce `any` to bypass errors.
- Validate external data at runtime.
- Prefer Server Components by default and Client Components only when interactivity/browser APIs require them.
- Keep secrets and privileged calls server-side.
- Do not trust hidden UI state for authorization.
- Represent money in integer minor units or validated decimal strings; format only at the presentation layer.
- Handle loading, empty, error, and retry states.
- Preserve accessibility: semantic elements, labels, keyboard use, focus, and contrast.
- Avoid unnecessary global state and premature memoization.
- Add focused tests for business-critical UI logic.
